  "prompt": "What are the top 10 books one must read before turning 20 something?",
  "response": "Reading is a fantastic way to gain wisdom, empathy, and perspective, especially in your formative years. Here\u2019s a list of 10 must-read books to explore before turning 20, covering a range of genres, themes, and life lessons:\n\n### 1. **\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee**  \n   - A powerful exploration of racial injustice, morality, and growing up in the American South. It teaches empathy and courage.\n\n### 2. **\"The Catcher in the Rye\" by J.D. Salinger**  \n   - A classic coming-of-age novel that captures teenage angst, rebellion, and the search for identity.\n\n### 3. **\"1984\" by George Orwell**  \n   - A dystopian masterpiece that explores themes of surveillance, totalitarianism, and the importance of truth and freedom.\n\n### 4. **\"Pride and Prejudice\" by Jane Austen**  \n   - A witty and timeless story about love, societal expectations, and personal growth.\n\n### 5. **\"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho**  \n   - A philosophical novel about following your dreams, finding your purpose, and embracing life\u2019s journey.\n\n### 6. **\"The Little Prince\" by Antoine de Saint-Exup\u00e9ry**  \n   - A poetic and profound tale about love, friendship, and the essence of life, perfect for all ages.\n\n### 7. **\"Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind\" by Yuval Noah Harari**  \n   - A thought-provoking exploration of human history, culture, and the forces that shaped our world.\n\n### 8. **\"The Book Thief\" by Markus Zusak**  \n   - A moving story set in Nazi Germany, told from the perspective of Death, about love, loss, and the power of words.\n\n### 9. **\"Harry Potter and the Sorcerer\u2019s Stone\" by J.K. Rowling**  \n   - The start of a magical series that teaches lessons about friendship, courage, and standing up for what\u2019s right.\n\n### 10. **\"The Perks of Being a Wallflower\" by Stephen Chbosky**  \n   - A heartfelt novel about adolescence, mental health, and the challenges of growing up.\n\n### Bonus Suggestions:\n   - **\"The Giver\" by Lois Lowry** (a thought-provoking take on conformity and individuality).  \n   - **\"The Diary of a Young Girl\" by Anne Frank** (a poignant first-hand account of resilience during WWII).  \n   - **\"Animal Farm\" by George Orwell** (a satirical allegory about power and corruption).  \n\nThese books offer a mix of classic literature, modern insights, and timeless wisdom that can help shape your worldview and inspire personal growth. Happy reading!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
